{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-00556/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-00556"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:05:56"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["establishing shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["exterior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A car parked in front of a townhouse."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00556/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-00556","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00556/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-00556"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00556/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00556/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00556/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00556/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00556/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00556/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00556/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00556/canvas/1/1dfb6533-f8b9-4b9a-818f-34afd32ed7de","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T13:15:19.298Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Number 3 Fitzroy Square served as the filming location for the atelier of the House of Woodcock. Located in central London just southeast of Regent’s Park, the area of Fitzrovia is known for its artistic affiliations. Notable inhabitants of Fitzroy Square itself include painters James McNeill Whistler, Ford Madox Brown, and Duncan Grant; National Gallery director Sir Charles Eastlake; playwright George Bernard Shaw; and writer Virginia Woolf. Prior to its conversion to a residential building, 3 Fitzroy Square was home to a publishing house and an independent film company (Vincent, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW212321736 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.telegraph.co.uk/films/2018/01/25/inside-phantom-threads-15-millon-house/\"><u>Daniel Day-Lewis slept here</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00556/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:493.3094812164581,666.5608228980325,491.45796064400713,267.16905187835425"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00556/canvas/1/3732ea78-275f-4bd0-bea9-f7142d6c81e2","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T13:15:35.228Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In an interview, Daniel Day-Lewis shared that he was eager to return to England in his work after shooting several American-set films: “‘England is deep in me. I’m made of that stuff. For a long time, a film set in England was too close to the world that I’d escaped from—drawing rooms, classic Shakespeare, <em>Downton Abbey </em>did not interest me. But I was fascinated by London after the war. My parents told stories about living through the Blitz, and I felt like I ingested that. I am sentimental about that world. And my dad was very much like Reynolds Woodcock. If a poet is not self-absorbed, what else is he?’” (Hirschberg, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW191082982 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.wmagazine.com/story/exclusive-daniel-day-lewis-giving-up-acting-phantom-thread\"><u>Daniel Day-Lewis Opens Up</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00556/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:689.0071556350625,432.89355992844384,114.21735241502688,198.91771019677986"}}}]}]}]}